This paper deals with the security and privacy of OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect, which are authentication and authorization protocols used in web applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the development of a vulnerability scanner and protector, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the privacy implications of OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect, which could be related to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the implementation of OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL).
